cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.FL, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the computation of winning sets for parity and Streett objectives, which are central problems in computer-aided verification and formal methods.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents improved algorithms for computing winning sets in graphs and game graphs.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with game graphs and winning conditions in games.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the verification of closed and open systems with strong fairness conditions, which can be modeled using automata and formal languages.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the synthesis of reactive systems, which can be seen as a programming language problem.
